benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: PUT Valid Request Coverage: Multiple TC01/TC02/TC03/TC13/TC14/TC15/TC17/TC22/TC23/TC24/TC25 demonstrate successful updates and state variations under normal, edge, and backward-compatibility scenarios (204 responses and updated data).

PUT Error Handling and Validation: Tests TC04 (invalid bundleId), TC05 (non-existent bundle), TC06 (missing required header), TC07 (malformed JSON), TC08 (missing body), TC09 (unsupported fields) validate 400/404 responses and proper error signaling.
Authorization and Security Coverage: TC10 (401 unauthorized) and TC12 (SQL injection) cover authorization and input sanitization concerns; TC02 also exercises optional headers.
Server/Dependency Failure Coverage: TC11 (503 service unavailable) and TC20 (500 internal server error) verify resilience to dependency failures and internal errors.
Performance/Resilience Coverage: TC17 (normal load), TC18 (peak load), and TC21 (transient network recovery) assess performance and recoverability under load and transient faults.
Edge Case Coverage: TC12 (security), TC19 (special characters), TC13 (max fields), TC14 (max length), TC15 (empty value), TC16 (extra URL parameter) test boundary conditions and input validation.

State Variation Coverage: TC22 (no existing custom fields), TC23 (update existing fields), TC24 (partial update), and TC25 (backward compatibility with older clients) cover various bundle states and update behaviors.
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling tests (e.g., 429 responses under burst traffic) are not covered.
Caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) on PUT responses are not covered.
Explicit 403 Forbidden tests for insufficient privileges beyond 401 are not covered.
Additional race-condition scenarios beyond high-concurrency (e.g., conflicting concurrent updates with versioning) are not explicitly covered.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to validate proper handling when user lacks sufficient privileges.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify 429 responses under burst traffic.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on PUT responses to validate caching semantics.
Include explicit race-condition/concurrency tests simulating simultaneous updates (with or without versioning) to ensure correct behavior under conflicts.
